post.description:
This endpoint is only available when GRV/Supplier Invoice split is enabled in Evolution defaults.
It receives stock into inventory and creates an archived GRV document plus an unprocessed Supplier Invoice.

Sample request for full stock receipt:

    POST /api/v1/purchasedocuments/123456789/process-stock
    {
      "processFullQuantities": true,
      "grvNumber": "GRV-2024-001"
    }

Sample request for partial stock receipt:

    POST /api/v1/purchasedocuments/123456789/process-stock
    {
      "processFullQuantities": false,
      "detailQuantities": [
        {
          "detailID": 987654321,
          "quantityToProcess": 5.0
        }
      ]
    }

The GRV will be archived and an unprocessed Supplier Invoice will be created for later processing.

This endpoint processes the entire purchase order - both stock receipt and supplier invoice posting.

Sample request for full processing:

    POST /api/v1/purchasedocuments/123456789/process
    {
      "processFullQuantities": true,
      "supplierInvoiceNumber": "SINV-2024-001"
    }

Sample request for partial processing:

    POST /api/v1/purchasedocuments/123456789/process
    {
      "processFullQuantities": false,
      "detailQuantities": [
        {
          "detailID": 987654321,
          "quantityToProcess": 5.0
        }
      ]
    }

Processing will receive stock and post transactions to all relevant ledgers.

Sample request for full processing:

    POST /api/v1/salesdocuments/123456789/process
    {
      "processFullQuantities": true,
      "invoiceNumber": "INV-2024-001",
      "processDate": "2024-01-15"
    }

Sample request for partial processing:

    POST /api/v1/salesdocuments/123456789/process
    {
      "processFullQuantities": false,
      "detailQuantities": [
        {
          "detailID": 987654321,
          "quantityToProcess": 5.0
        }
      ]
    }

Processing will create an invoice and post transactions to all relevant ledgers.

Sample request:

    POST /api/v1/salesdocuments/123456789/convert-to-order
    {
      "orderNumber": "SO-2024-001",
      "processImmediately": false
    }

Sample request with immediate processing:

    POST /api/v1/salesdocuments/123456789/convert-to-order
    {
      "processImmediately": true,
      "processingOptions": {
        "processFullQuantities": true,
        "invoiceNumber": "INV-2024-001"
      }
    }

The quote will be converted to a sales order. If processImmediately is true,
the order will also be processed into an invoice.
